checking the IQR for numerical variables

Source: https://www.statology.org/find-outliers-in-r/

Age

Age has zero outliers.

Q1 = quantile(uci$Age, .25)
Q3 = quantile(uci$Age, .75)
IQR = IQR(uci$Age)

age_outliers = subset(uci, uci$Age<(Q1 - 1.5*IQR) | uci$Age>(Q3 + 1.5*IQR))

age_outliers
